# Project Structure

When introducing changes to the project, always follow the directory structure below:

- `./src` - source code
- `./src/layouts` - Astro layouts
- `./src/pages` - Astro pages
- `./src/pages/api` - API endpoints
- `./src/middleware/index.ts` - Astro middleware
- `./src/types.ts` - Shared types
- `./src/components` - Shared client-side components written in Astro (static) and React (dynamic)
- `./src/components/ui` - Client-side components from shadcn/ui
- `./src/lib` - Services and helpers 
- `./src/assets` - static internal assets
- `./public` - public assets

When modifying the directory structure, always update this structure.

## Organize code in feature directories

Each feature has its separate folder in `src` directory. Feature is independent block of application. An examples of features are listed in `example-features`- when implementing new features look into these folders and treat it as an benchmark for next features implementation.

<example-features>
src/flow-chart
src/depositors-list
src/depositors-list-item
</example-features>

In case of `src/depositors-list` the `<feature_name>` is `depositors-list`. 

The structure of feature directory:
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.tsx` - main file with the actual React component to import, contains context provider
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.context.tsx` - the context to avoid drilling props and also for exposing all data, state and logic.
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.utils.tsx` - file containg other functions (like formatters, accessors, mappers) and constants, optional, don't create if empty
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.params.tsx` - hook for all data shared in the context
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.types.tsx` - local type definitions, use only for types shared across at least two files, optional, don't create if empty
- `src/<feature_name>/<feature_name>.stories.tsx` - Storybook file for `<feature_name>.tsx` 
- `src/<feature_name>/queries` - directory for hooks which use `useQuery` hook from `@tanstack/react-query` if the feature has any
- `src/<feature_name>/hooks` - directory for other local custom hooks, optional, don't create if empty
- `src/<feature_name>/components` - directory for local components, if jsx block has more than 3 lines, extract a component

All the data and logic should be handled in hooks.

Feature can be also meant as separate Astro island.




